Anambra State Commissioner for Culture, Tourism and Entertainment Hon. Don Onyenji has said that the government of Professor Charles Chukwuma Soludo plans to build a world-class tourism and leisure park at Agulu Lake in the Anaocha Local Government Area of the state. Onyenji a seasoned broadcaster of 41 years standing who disclosed the plan to our correspondent in Awka, said the tourism and leisure park when it is built will be a major tourist destination and would also be a veritable source of clientele for the Golden Tulip Hotel situated in the Agulu Lake environment. He said the governor is passionate about the project as it is in line with the vision and mission to create a liveable, lovable and prosperous new Anambra conducive and congenial for everyone, adding that there are a lot of things in the tourism sector yet unknown which he said would be unravelled by the Soludo administration. The Commissioner said that the present state government is working horizontally and vertically across all sectors of Anambra economy and that the government is already succeeding as he was optimistic that when what is on the ground germinates, Ndi-Anambra would be perplexed at the quantum of positive results they would see, adding that the Soludo administration is coming with huge surprises. Onyenji also hinted that the ministry received visitors from the Federal Ministry of Information and Culture, National Tourism Development Commission and National Museums and Monuments, who visited Ogbunike Cafe the in Oyi local government area of the state and testified to its global appeal and revenue potential. He said efforts have been intensified to place Ogbunike Cafe on a UNICEF global heritage site where the entire world would visit and appreciate the gift of nature in the Cafe as a major destination for tourists all over the world. Apart from the Ogbunike Cafe, the Commissioner noted that other tourist sites across Anambra state like the Oba-Ukwu Cafe and Waterfalls at Owerre-Ezukala, Igboukwu Museum, Zik Mausoleum in Onitsha and some others would be upgraded to international standard while communities will produce their own heritage sites so that those who are yet unknown would be known. -Advertisement- POLL Again, he said that the development of the tourist sites in the state would amount to employment opportunities for the citizenry, boost the revenue of the state and most importantly attract the traffic of tourists from all over the world to Anambra state for leisure and expeditions.